==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Immutable
<hw>Im*mu"ta*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>immutabilis</ets>; pref. <ets>im-</ets> not + <ets>mutabilis</ets>
mutable. See <er>Mutable</er>.]</ety> <def>Not mutable; not capable or
susceptible of change; unchangeable; unalterable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That by two <qex>immutable</qex> things, in which it was
impossible for God to lie, we might have a strong consolation.</q>
<rj><qau>Heb. vi. 18.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Immutable</qex>, immortal, infinite,⟦br⟧
Eternal King.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Im*mu"ta*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>Im*mu"ta*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 733 --></p>

<p><ent>Immutate</ent>⟦br⟧
